# HTML_CSS
HTML+CSS

e.g.
/* padding内边距 */
p {
  border: 3px solid #A2D3F4;
  padding: 10px;
}

p {
  border: 3px solid #XXXXXX;
  padding: 5px 10px 5px 10px;
}

refer to the amount of padding in a clockwise rotation
it specifies the amount of padding on the top (5 pixels), right (10 pixels), 
bottom (5 pixels), and left (10 pixels)sides of the content

shortcut:

p {
  padding: 5px 10px;
}

padding-top
padding-right
padding-bottom
padding-left

/* margin外边距 */

p {
  border: 1px solid #23AD44;
  margin: 20px;
}

p {
  margin: 6px 12px 6px 12px;
}

p {
  margin: 6px 12px;
}

margin-top
margin-right
margin-bottom
margin-left

/* 元素居中 */
div.headline {
  margin: auto;
}


* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}
Many developers choose to reset these default values so that they can truly work with a clean slate.


Inline elements 
Block-level elements

inline 
block 
inline-block
none 

/* visibility */

.future {
  visibility: hidden;
}

hidden - hides an element.
visible - displays an element.
